<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName LSID="F18BF010-E050-5E2B-B52A-012ABF5D1BBC" authority="H. Scholz, Willdenowia 11 (1): 96. 1981." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa medica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medica">Eremopoa medica H. Scholz, Willdenowia 11(1): 96. 1981.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
Persia, Prov. Azerbaijan occid.: In pratis paludosis SE Shahpur versus lacum Rezaiyeh (Urmia), 1300 m; 12 Jun 1971, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Rechinger 41820</emphasis>
(holotype: W [W1972-0000975 image!; isotypes: B! [B 10_0272774], GZU [GZU000201751 image!], WU [WU0033125 image!]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
The type collection of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Eremopoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eremopoa medica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="medica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Eremopoa medica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly a perennial species of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Puccinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Puccinellia" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Puccinellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(possibly 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. gigantea" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. gigantea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Grossh.) Grossh.) with lemmas rounded on the back, a distinct short crown of callus hairs and papillae common on vegetative structures (pedicels and leaves). Material cited as 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. persica" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. medica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="medica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">E. medica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rahmanian, S" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Botany" pageId="22" pageNumber="91" pagination="8 - 15" refId="B43" refString="Rahmanian, S, Saeidi, H, Assadi, M, Rahiminejad, MR, 2014. A taxonomic revision of the genus Eremopoa Roschv. (Poaceae, Poeae) in Iran. Iranian Journal of Botany 20 (1): 8 - 15" title="A taxonomic revision of the genus Eremopoa Roschv. (Poaceae, Poeae) in Iran." volume="20" year="2014">Rahmanian et al. (2014</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 5) appears to us to be 
<taxonomicName authority="subsp. persica" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Poa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Poa persica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica" subspecies="persica">Poa persica subsp. persica</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
; their description and illustration indicate an annual habit, pubescent lemmas and panicles with 10 or more branches per whorl. The single specimen (TARI 35082) cited was included in our molecular analysis and formed a clade with other 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. persica" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
accessions in all trees.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="88" type="invalid names, not vouchered">
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Invalid names, not vouchered</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Royle" authorityYear="1840" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Festuca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Festuca amherstiana" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amherstiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Festuca amherstiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nees, Ill. Bot. Himal. Mts. 417. 1839, nom. nud., name in list, no voucher.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="19" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Notes.</emphasis>
Kew GrassBase (Clayton et al. 2002+) indicates it is equal to 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" genus="E." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="E. persica" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">E. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen K00078950 (ex P) (image!), 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">Voyage V. Jacquemont aux Indes orient. no. 1902</emphasis>
, has this name on the label. The specimen is certainly 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. diaphora" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="diaphora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. diaphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. persica" pageId="19" pageNumber="88" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="88">P. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
